OL,3,CMan whose brother died of MND
OL,4,C'emotional' as major landmark lit up
OL,5,Cin his memory
OL,7,FThe brother of a man who died from
OL,8,Fmotor neurone disease (MND) said he
OL,9,Ffelt 'emotional' that a major landmark
OL,10,Fwould once again be lit up in his
OL,11,Fbrother's memory.
OL,13,FRob Barrie, from Runcorn, was 31 when
OL,14,Fhe died from the disease in 2023.
OL,16,FHis brother Tom, had the idea last
OL,17,Fyear of lighting up the Mersey Gateway
OL,18,FBridge to mark global motor neurone
OL,19,Fdisease awareness day.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/5
